d 'NARAYANP': module to implement Narayan-Popp (2010) unit root test with two structural breaks
d
d      narayanp performs the Narayan and Popp (2010) Augmented
d Dickey-Fuller-type test for a unit root that allows for two
d structural	breaks at unknown dates. The data-generating
d process is written as an unobserved-components model in which the
d breaks are	modelled as innovational outliers, so that a break
d takes effect gradually rather than instantaneously (Narayan and
d Popp 2010,	Eqs. 1-6). The test allows for breaks under both
d the unit-root null and the trend-stationary alternative, which
d reduces the	 spurious rejections that affect earlier ADF-type
d break tests.	  Two specifications are available, both for
d trending data: model M1 allows two breaks in the level, and model
d M2 allows two    breaks in the level and in the slope. In both
d cases the test statistic is the t-ratio on the coefficient of
d y(t-1); the	 unit-root null is rho = 1. 
d
d KW: unit root tests
d KW: structural breaks
d
d Requires: Stata version 14
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260707
d
d Author: Ozan Eruygur,  Ankara Haci Bayram Veli University
d Support: email eruygur@@gmail.com
d
f narayanp.ado
f narayanp.sthlp
